article.headline: IUPUI 62, Indiana St. 41
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- John Avery had 15 points and 13 rebounds to lead IUPUI to a 62-41 victory over Indiana State on Tuesday. The Jaguars (7-4) held Indiana State to 33 percent shooting as the Sycamores didn't score in the final 4:27 of the game. Alex Young also scored 15 for IUPUI, hitting two 3-pointers as the Jaguars went on an 8-2 run to start the second half and open up a 41-28 lead. Avery scored eight points during a 13-2 IUPUI run in the first half that wiped out a 16-12 Indiana State lead. Jordan Printy led the Sycamores (2-9) with 15 points as he shot 5-of-7 on 3-pointers. The Jaguars, who won a 67-65 buzzer-beater over Seton Hall on Saturday, outrebounded Indiana State 42-24, including 16 offensive rebounds. Gary Patterson added 10 points for IUPUI and Rashad Reed had 10 points for Indiana State.
